<class 'int'>


======================================= 

weight = input("enter your weight in kg: ")
height = input("enter your height in m: ")
#print(type(height))                          #str so we need to convert to int
bmi = int(weight) / float(height) ** 2        #o/p is float if you want to add to print as part of string first you need to convert int to str then only we can add 
#print(BMI)
#print(type(BMI))
bmi_as_int = str(bmi)
print("person's bmi is " + bmi_as_int)
#print(type(bmi_as_int))


O/P:

enter your weight in kg: 56
enter your height in m: 5
person's bmi is 2.24
















